Devon and Cornwall Police are appealing for witnesses after controlled drugs were stolen from a south Devon pharmacy, in the early hours of Wednesday morning.Officers said a man was seen gaining entry to the shop in Churchill Court, Brixham, at about 01:25 BST.In a separate incident, three men were seen entering a supermarket in Borough Close, Paignton and stealing cigarettes and alcohol at about 05:15 BST.Inquiries into both burglaries are ongoing and police have asked any one with relevant information to contact them.
